Usage:
There are two ways to run the program:
1. In root directory, do the following commands:
   sudo docker-compose up
2. In the directory /code, do the following:
   make
   ./proxy

Please note that the proxy starts as a daemon if run outside the docker

Please send all request to port 12345 on the machine where the proxy is running.

Log for your activity is inside /code directory.

Firefox Http Proxy Configuration:
1. Select Manual proxy configuration
2. In the box of "HTTP Proxy", enter the IP/host address of the machine which the proxy is running on
3. In the box of "Port", enter 12345
4. Check "Use this proxy server for all protocols" (optional)
5. Hit "OK"